cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.SY, cs.DS

The paper deals with community detection in networks using both connectivity and continuous attribute information. This falls under the scope of social network analysis and machine learning, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. Specifically, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as it directly deals with network analysis and community detection. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper involves learning parameters for the stochastic block model. cs.SD (Sound) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are less likely but still possible as they deal with signal processing and control theory, which can be applied to network analysis. Finally, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a possibility as the paper involves developing a new model for community detection.
